clusterList.phrase: it was greg fox he told me he was on the radio over in hattiesburg we hit it off pretty good a year or so later he went to work for carnegie a while later i left carnegie and with a friend of mine we started our own business of motivational talks it was called the success center and we sold it all over the world oil rigs on the north sea alaska europe all over louisiana we did it the old fashioned way we wouldn't take no for an answer we believed in what we were doing and we were as enthusiastic as all get out
